sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry
    participant KServe as KServe Controller
    participant OdhMC as odh-model-controller
    participant S3 as Object Storage (S3)
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway
    participant KRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy
    participant VLLM as vLLM Model Server
    participant Client as External Client

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 1: Model Serving (Single-Model Inference)

    User->>Dashboard: Login via kube-rbac-proxy<br/>(TokenReview + SAR)
    Dashboard-->>User: Show model registry & serving UI

    %% Model registration
    User->>Dashboard: Register model in Model Registry
    Dashboard->>ModelReg: Create RegisteredModel +<br/>ModelVersion + ModelArtifact<br/>(REST 8080 or gRPC 9090)
    ModelReg->>ModelReg: Store in MySQL/PostgreSQL

    %% Deploy model
    User->>Dashboard: Deploy model as InferenceService
    Dashboard->>KServe: Create InferenceService CR<br/>(K8s API)
    KServe->>KServe: Create Deployment with<br/>vLLM container + storage initializer
    KServe->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>(HTTPS, AWS IAM)
    KServe->>Gateway: Create HTTPRoute +<br/>optional AuthPolicy
    OdhMC->>OdhMC: Watch InferenceService
    OdhMC->>OdhMC: Create Route, NetworkPolicy,<br/>ServiceMonitor
    OdhMC->>ModelReg: Sync deployment status<br/>(optional)

    %% Inference
    Client->>Gateway: POST /v2/models/my-model/infer<br/>(HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+)
    Gateway->>KRBAC: Forward to kube-rbac-proxy<br/>(8443)
    KRBAC->>KRBAC: TokenReview + SAR validation<br/>(FIPS 140-2 TLS)
    KRBAC->>VLLM: Proxy to model server<br/>(8000)
    VLLM-->>KRBAC: Prediction result
    KRBAC-->>Gateway: Response
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON response<br/>(HTTPS)

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Notebook as Jupyter Notebook
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant DSP as DS Pipelines API
    participant DSPO as DS Pipelines Operator
    participant Argo as Argo Workflows
    participant S3 as Object Storage
    participant MLMD as ML Metadata
    participant KServe as KServe

    Note over User,KServe: Workflow 2: ML Pipeline Execution

    User->>Dashboard: Create pipeline via UI
    Dashboard->>DSP: Submit pipeline definition<br/>(REST 8888)

    alt From Notebook
        User->>Notebook: Import KFP SDK
        Notebook->>DSP: Submit pipeline via SDK<br/>(REST 8888)
    end

    DSP->>DSP: Compile pipeline IR<br/>(Argo Workflow spec)
    DSP->>Argo: Create Workflow CR

    loop Each Pipeline Step
        Argo->>Argo: Create pod for step<br/>(argoexec sidecar)
        Note over Argo: Driver: resolve inputs,<br/>check execution cache
        Argo->>S3: Download input artifacts<br/>(HTTPS)
        Note over Argo: Launcher: execute user code
        Argo->>S3: Upload output artifacts<br/>(HTTPS)
    end

    Argo->>DSP: Persistence Agent watches<br/>Workflow status
    DSP->>MLMD: Persist run state +<br/>artifact metadata<br/>(gRPC 8080)
    DSP->>S3: Store pipeline artifacts

    %% Optional model deployment
    Note over DSP,KServe: Optional: auto-deploy trained model
    DSP->>KServe: Create InferenceService CR

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as ML Engineer
    participant SDK as CodeFlare SDK
    participant CF as CodeFlare Operator
    participant Kueue as Kueue Controller
    participant KubeRay as KubeRay Operator
    participant RayHead as Ray Head Pod
    participant RayWorker as Ray Worker Pods
    participant CertMgr as cert-manager
    participant OAuth as OAuth Proxy

    Note over User,OAuth: Workflow 3: Distributed Training with Batch Scheduling

    User->>SDK: Define training job<br/>(resource requirements, GPU count)
    SDK->>CF: Submit RayCluster wrapped<br/>in AppWrapper CR

    CF->>Kueue: Create Workload for<br/>quota admission
    Kueue->>Kueue: Evaluate ClusterQueue/<br/>Cohort hierarchy
    alt Resources Available
        Kueue-->>CF: Admit Workload
    else Resources Unavailable
        Kueue-->>CF: Queue Workload<br/>(wait for quota)
        Note over Kueue: Preemption or borrowing<br/>from Cohort if configured
        Kueue-->>CF: Admit Workload (later)
    end

    CF->>KubeRay: Create RayCluster CR
    KubeRay->>CertMgr: Request CA certificate<br/>(per-RayCluster CA hierarchy)
    CertMgr-->>KubeRay: Issue CA + node certs
    KubeRay->>RayHead: Create head pod<br/>(GCS 6379, Dashboard 8265,<br/>Client 10001)
    KubeRay->>RayWorker: Create worker pods<br/>(GPU-enabled)

    CF->>RayHead: Inject OAuth proxy sidecar<br/>(8443, OpenShift OAuth)
    CF->>RayHead: Inject mTLS init container<br/>(openssl self-signed or cert-manager)

    Note over RayHead,RayWorker: mTLS between all Ray nodes

    CF->>CF: Create NetworkPolicy<br/>(deny-all + allow head-worker)
    CF->>CF: Create Route for<br/>Ray Dashboard access

    User->>OAuth: Access Ray Dashboard<br/>(HTTPS/443)
    OAuth->>OAuth: OpenShift OAuth +<br/>SAR (pods:get)
    OAuth->>RayHead: Proxy to Dashboard<br/>(8265)

    User->>RayHead: Submit training job<br/>(Ray Client 10001)
    RayHead->>RayWorker: Distribute tasks<br/>(mTLS, NCCL)
    RayWorker-->>RayHead: Training results

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Platform User
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant KServe as KServe Controller
    participant VLLM_P as vLLM Prefill Pods
    participant VLLM_D as vLLM Decode Pods
    participant Scheduler as llm-d-inference-scheduler
    participant KVCache as llm-d-kv-cache
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service Operator
    participant Orchestrator as FMS Guardrails Orchestrator
    participant Detectors as Guardrails Detectors
    participant Client as API Client

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 4: LLM Serving with Guardrails (Disaggregated P/D)

    User->>Dashboard: Create LLMInferenceService<br/>(guardrails label, P/D topology)
    Dashboard->>KServe: Create LLMInferenceService CR

    KServe->>VLLM_P: Create prefill Deployment<br/>(or LeaderWorkerSet for multi-node)
    KServe->>VLLM_D: Create decode Deployment
    KServe->>Scheduler: Configure llm-d-inference-scheduler<br/>as Envoy ext-proc sidecar
    KServe->>KVCache: Configure KV transfer<br/>between P/D (gRPC)

    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Auto-detect guardrails label<br/>on InferenceService
    TrustyAI->>Orchestrator: Generate orchestrator config<br/>(detector endpoints, TLS settings)

    Note over Orchestrator,Detectors: Guardrails pipeline ready

    Client->>Scheduler: POST inference request<br/>(HTTPS, Kuadrant AuthPolicy)
    Scheduler->>Scheduler: Evaluate KV-cache utilization,<br/>prefix cache affinity,<br/>queue depth
    Scheduler->>Orchestrator: Route to guardrails first

    Orchestrator->>Detectors: Content safety check<br/>(HuggingFace classifiers,<br/>LLM Judge)
    Detectors-->>Orchestrator: Detection results

    alt Content Safe
        Orchestrator->>VLLM_P: Forward to prefill<br/>(optimal backend)
        VLLM_P->>KVCache: Transfer KV cache<br/>(gRPC)
        KVCache->>VLLM_D: KV cache to decode pod
        VLLM_D-->>Orchestrator: Generated response
        Orchestrator->>Detectors: Output safety check
        Detectors-->>Orchestrator: Output safe
        Orchestrator-->>Client: Final response
    else Content Blocked
        Orchestrator-->>Client: Content blocked response
    end
